{
  "name": "disasters: a pop-losing disaster trims the workers array to the new pop",
  "notes": "workers>pop fix (reviewer #2314): a FAMINE (33% pop loss) on a fully-worked city must trim its workers array to the reduced pop — starvation + settler pop-cost already do, disasters were the gap, breaking the workers.length<=pop invariant and aborting archipelago sims. Grassland-only + aqueduct (blocks fire+plague) + no granary => famine is the only eligible disaster; the food buffer prevents starvation so the ONLY pop change is the famine. disastersEnabled + rngState 72 fire it deterministically. Hash-only cross-language pin; semantics asserted in test/disasters.test.js.",
